don't want to sleep. note: ticker holder of this class can go to the vip waiting room at station. hard sleepers (硬卧 yìngwò), on the other hand, have 3 beds per column open to the corridor. the highest bunk is very high up and leaves little space for headroom. taller travelers (6'3" and above) may find this to be the best bunk since when sleeping your feet will extend into the passageway and they will not be bumped. the top bunk is also useful for people with things to hide (e.g. cameras). when placed by your head they are harder 